This paper discusses learning deterministic policies in continuous domains using a novel policy update approach. The paper focuses on theoretical justification and analysis of the approach, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
